  "title": "Applying CSS styles to connectMenu item removes \"isRefined\" functionality",
  "body": "Hi! I took for example this tutorial from official documentation: [Customize widgets](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/customization.html)\r\n\r\nRemade it to suit my needs, basically just changed `<select>` to `<ul>` and `<option>` to `<li>`.\r\n\r\nNow when trying to customize `<li>` (which is connectMenu Item) through CSS, somehow magically \"isRefined\" stop working and does not apply class to `<li>`. I spent like 2 days figuring out and coming up to this point.\r\n\r\n",
